cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.DB

The paper proposes a new hybrid model for collaborative filtering that leverages content information and implicit user feedback. This involves matrix factorization and contractive auto-encoder paradigm. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the paper deals with personalized recommendations, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves modeling user behavior, cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it involves natural language processing, and cs.DB (Databases) as it involves handling large-scale datasets.
